org.gljiva.trPuzzleCorner.p2006nd3
Class Rect3

java.lang.Object
  org.gljiva.trPuzzleCorner.p2006nd3.Rect3
All Implemented Interfaces:
Cloneable
public class Rect3
extends Object
implements Cloneable

A 3x3 rectangular grid made up of 4 3-digit numbers (and a hole in the middle). Yes, I know that an NxN rectangle is usually called a square, but in this case it would be confusing because each of the 3-digit numbers is also a square (i.e. it equals x*x for some integer x). Deal with it.

Author:
bert
